<TITLE> Coco first to see body of Toyeba </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)  The body of former prime minister Khaleda Zia's mother Toyeba Majumdar arrived in Dhaka Saturday afternoon. Khaleda's son Arafat Rahman Coco was the first to see the body of his grandmother. He was led into Khaleda's cantonment home at 4:36pm, IG (prisons) Zakir Hassan told bdnews24.com. He left the place at 5.48pm. The official said the threeKhaleda and sons Tarique Rahman and Cocowould not be allowed to see the body together. They may not take part in the namaz-e-janaza for Toyeba at Azad Mosque in Gulshan. Zakir Hassan said Khaleda Zia would get two hours to stay beside her mother's body. Tarique and Coco would get one hour each. He said their parole could be extended to 9pm. bdnews24.
